Tiefling concept LoRA

Making models can be expensive. Do you like what I do? Consider supporting me on Patreon 🅿️ or feel free to buy me a coffee ☕

I had a lot of fun using it. Should work around weight 1.

Some examples are too "sexy". You need to register to see them.


How to use LoRA's in auto1111:

  • Update webui (use git pull like here or redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to change the weight (by default it's :1 which is usually too high)

items.name: Ornella Muti
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Ornella Muti (née Francesca Romana Rivelli) is an Italian actress, perhaps best known for her role as Princess Aura in 1980's Flash Gordon.

This is a 130-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (0rnellamut1:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Catherine Bach ('Daisy Duke' era - 1979-83 - CHECKPOINT)
items.description:
THERE IS A LORA VERSION OF THIS MODEL AVAILABLE. IT IS EXACTLY THE SAME MODEL AS THIS ONE, EXCEPT IN A DIFFERENT AND LIGHTER FORMAT.

Shivam Dreambooth of the 1970s-80s Dukes of Hazzard actress, using 200 ref images and 1800 (real) reg images, for 12,000 steps.

No nudes were in the training data, so while the model may sometimes produce some racy images, it is not likely to produce truly NSFW output by default.

I generally use these models in complex workflows, inpainting faces after initial T2Is, and using ControlNet extensively. So if you're hoping for one-click prompt magic, my models aren't data-curated with this in mind, but rather as tools for traditional workflows that use Photoshop and other older methods.

items.name: Futura Madison Beer (natural look)
items.description:
My rating vs expectation: 93%

(High quality dataset. Likeness is good, but not perfect and there's room for improvement. Perhaps I could push the training to 500 epochs.)

All TIs I make depict real adults. Please apply it with good judgement. If you're the model and want this removed reach out to me via link below. I welcome all criticisms and suggestions with curiosity. If you like my work, buy me a house:
https://ko-fi.com/futurafree

Yes, another one of Madison. But I trained this TI with the goal of achieving a more natural look. Her photos in recent memories are typically makeup heavy and exaggerated. The dataset used for this contains many no-makeup photos from younger years (18, 19, 20) to aid with that.

This TI was trained in sd1.5 base with 5 vectors, 26 images, 9775 steps, and 376 epochs. This was finetuned for epiCRealism evo3 and Realistic Vision V4.0, but may work on others.

TIPS:

  • MUST be the first word in the prompt for likeness and consistency.

    • Example: futuramadison9775v5, portrait of a woman, long dress etc.

    • Not: Portrait of futuramadison9775v5, etc.

  • Recommended strength:

    • (0.98-1.0)

  • I use adetailer for all images, with mediapipe_face_full, blank pos and neg, 1024x1024, inpaint mask blur: 20, inpaint noise strength: 0.45.

  • Again, prompt in adetailer is left blank most of the time; (*exception*: if Loras/Lycoris is used and has significant impact on the appearance of the model's face, copy paste pos prompt without Loras/Lycoris into adetailer).

  • Upscaler I use: 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k.

Commander James Bond CMG is a fictional Senior Operational Officer of the Double-O Section, an ultra-covert Black Ops unit within the Secret Intelligence Service (SIS/MI6). As an agent of MI6, Bond holds cryptonym "007". The '00' prefix indicates his discretionary licence to kill in the performance of his duties. He was created and developed by the British author and former naval intelligence officier Ian Fleming.

Sean Connery was the first actor to perform the role on the cinematographic adaptations. He was doubled by stuntmen Bob Simmons, George Leech, Alf Joint, and Bell Rocket Belt test pilot William P. Suitor.[1] He appeared in Dr. No (1962), From Russia with Love (1963), Goldfinger (1964), Thunderball (1965), You Only Live Twice (1967) and Diamonds Are Forever (1971). In 1983, he returned to the role for the last time in the non-EON Productions James Bond film, Never Say Never Again. In addition Connery also provided his voice and likeness for 2005's video game adaptation of From Russia with Love.

items.name: Etrian Odyssey / Himukai Yuuji Style
items.description:
This is the LyCORIS version of the previously released LoRA. It's trained on the same dataset but should generate higher quality output while being more flexible.

How to use
The style will work even if you just prompt "1girl" or "1boy" but you can refine it further by using fantasy/Etrian Odyssey related tags. Or not if you want to use contemporary themes or just apply a general Himukai Yuuji style influence.
For more prompting tips see the sample images or the uploaded zip with training tags.

AUTOMATIC1111 users can utilize the wildcard prompt below to randomly prompt classes and races from the game. I recommend using "3d" and "realistic" in negatives on AOM2 and other models with mixed in realism. Not really needed in this version for AOM2, other models may still need it.
"Chibi" also seems to work fine for more chubby little adventurers.

<lora:EtrianV2:1>
({full|upper} body)
(solo)
(1girl)(facing viewer)
({human|elf|bunny_ear|goat_horns|horse_ears|cat_ears|demon|angel} girl)
in ({barbarian|bard|cleric|druid|fighter|monk|paladin|ranger|rogue|sorcerer|warlock|wizard|artificer} outfit)

Don't forget to review and upload your own images, it's always fun to see what you're creating!

MISC
Trained on 44 images on NAI at 512 resolution.
All sample images are raw txt2img upscaled, no inpainting or helper embeddings used.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist if you want the good stuff.

A request of @alextravis8888729.

Genevieve 'Genny' Shawcross is an American social media personality who gained notoriety during her recent stint on Love Island America.

180-step TI trained on a dataset of 9 images with these settings. (Remember that my gradient = number of images in the dataset, so in this case it was reduced to 9.)

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (g3nshaw2:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Domination world
items.description:
General mix's successor animation model!

Feel free to propose any suggestions or opinions in 820725763 (QQ group) during use!

It integrates multiple models of both realist and animated styles, adopts MBW hierarchical merging, and incorporates the self-trained Earth OL style, capable of producing three schools of D3/2.5D/2D.

Unlike the Everything Furnace, the images it produces are more stable and support extreme resolution magnification.

Guaranteed that 3840×3840's i2i and 2560×2560's t2i won't have a lot of crashes when opening Hires. fix.

Recommended parameters are similar to Animated models of General mix's:

DPM++ 2M SDE Karras Sampling method,

Don't exceed 768px for direct image resolution,

It is recommended to add Bad hands-5 to reduce the probability of bad hands,

Using R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, i2i can give this model an effect superior to Hires. fix,

For magnification, tile VAE is recommended instead of direct magnification, can reach up to 5120×5120 with CNT without color stratification,

Image aspect ratios shouldn't exceed 16:9 or 9:16, else there will be severe crashes.

Improvements:

Fixed ugly mouth appearance, though it may still look bad in some cases,

The model is more likely to hide hands,

Changed the trigger word, now to make realistic images only need Photos, real ones two trigger words, to do animation, you need to use Anime, Illustration for reinforcement,

Improved NSFW character representation, plus realist content,

More sensitive to scene tags, significantly improved details, clearer distant content.

Negative Optimization:

The ability of animated style sfw representation is worse, and the scene doesn't have the gloss of Animated models of General Mix,

Always wants to draw people on landscape pictures,

Add ((3D modeling)),((3D style)),((three-dimensionality)) at the end of the tag

Recommended output parameters

DPM++ 2M SDE Karras

50-70 steps

CFG7-12

Recommended image ratio

Horizontal 16:9, 9:16

Vertical 8:5, 5:8

Or square 1:1

Do not use 4:3 or 3:4, otherwise, the face is very likely to mess up.

Resolution within 768

60+ steps can automatically fix the face without additional facial repair enabled.

HD restoration suggestion

Magnification 1.5-3 times

Restoration method 4x-AnimeSharp

40-60 steps

Redraw amplitude 0.45-0.6

Regular drafts can usually achieve effects better than HD restoration.

Magnification 2-4 times

Restoration method 4x-AnimeSharp

50-70 steps

Redraw amplitude 0.3-0.45

Other specifications

This model doesn't need to add a long section of quality TAGs, if you need style TAGs, use the ones I recommended.

This model doesn't need AVE, it will lead to over-color fitting.

items.name: SnoutMix
items.description:
NOTE, NEEDS THESE EMBEDDINGS FOR NEGATIVE PROMPTS

Use the above link for the Furtastic negative prompt embeddings, or images will not come out like in the showcase ones. Things will be very 2D without the embeddings.

Differences: Each version is like a variant. V1 is extremely realistic but rigid. V2 and V3 increasingly trade this in for more variety, better poses and expressions, and better NSFW acts. All are viable and have their own merits.

Introducing SnoutMix

A Mix of non-Furry and Furry models to create a great variety of anthro options, but bringing out more detail, still giving a lot of freedom to customise the human aspects, and having great backgrounds, with a focus on something more realistic. A big focus of this model is the transformation aspect, as it reacts well to E621 prompts and is perfect for inpainting those TF/Furry details. Works well with realistic character loras.

The gallery images are often inpainted, but you will get something very similar if copying their data directly. They are inpainted using the same model.

Usage Instructions:

This model performs best when still using the negative embeddings (see link in description). DO NOT use restore faces.Use the gallery for examples of how you can structure prompts that it agrees with.

V1-3 Like ClipSkip 2. Later ones prefer ClipSkip 1.

Recommended steps: 30-40.

Sampler: DPM++ 2M Karras
CFG Scale ~6 is what I use for reference images.

I don't use Hi-Res Fix, I use Controlnet Tiled instead.

Recommended smallest image size is around 640x640, seems very comfy with 640x768/640x888. SnoutMix 4 and beyond is okay with higher native res (about 800x1120 / 1024x1024 seems to be the stable limit)

VAE is not baked in, but vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.safetensors is highly recommended.
